         <div type="traslation">
            <head>Translation</head>
            <p>The handwriting of Cittampalavaṉ [who is] in the lineage (<foreign
                  xml:lang="tam-Latn">cantati</foreign>) of the vicuvaku (?) of Pātūr. There should
                  (<foreign xml:lang="tam-Latn">kaṭavatu</foreign>) be the support of the
               illustrious lotus-like feet of Ñāṉatecikaṉ. Jovian year Viya, which occurs in the
               [gap] Kaliyuka year, month of Tai, 4th day, [constellation of] Rokaṇi (rokaṇi-y-um) –
               [the manuscript] was fully copied. May the teacher thrive, there should (<foreign
                  xml:lang="tam-Latn">kaṭavatu</foreign>) be the support of the teacher. Having
               checked the copy of Amuṟtapāṇit Tampiraṉ, who is in Pommapuri, [this manuscript] was
               copied (eḻu†ti†tu, read as <foreign xml:lang="tam-Latn">eḻutiṉatu</foreign>?).</p>
         </div>

